The paper is about texture synthesis using generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is a popular topic in computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) research. The paper also discusses the architecture and properties of the proposed model, which falls under the category of machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI). Finally, the paper presents experiments with different types of texture images, which involves image processing and multimedia (MM) techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.GR, followed by cs.LG, cs.AI, and cs.MM.
